      'Holiness is not mainly for dramatic moments. It is forged in small, faithful, daily love.',
    formationText:
      'Most of the Christian life is not lived on mountaintops. It is lived in ordinary days: work, family, errands, tiredness, small kindnesses. Discipleship means letting Jesus be Lord of exactly these things, offering each one to him.\n\nThe saints remind us that holiness grows in faithful little acts done with love. A patient word, an honest hour of work, a quiet prayer, a hidden sacrifice. None of it is wasted when offered to God.\n\nYou do not need to wait for a perfect life to begin following Jesus. You begin where you are, with what today actually holds, and you offer it all to him.',
