    formationText:
      'Good intentions fade without a rhythm to carry them. A simple rule of life gives our faith a steady shape so it can grow over years, not just good days. It need not be complicated.\n\nThree anchors hold most of it together. Prayer: a little time with God each day, morning and evening. Sacraments: regular Mass and Confession, where grace is poured out. Charity: concrete love for the people around us and the poor.\n\nStart small and be faithful rather than ambitious and inconsistent. The journey of faith is a long walk with God, and a gentle, steady rhythm will take you further than bursts of zeal.',
