    summary: "Original sin is not a personal crime we committed. It is a wound in human nature we are born into, and Christ heals it.",
    formationText: "At the beginning, humanity was created in friendship with God, in a state of holiness we call original justice. By turning from God, our first parents lost that gift, not only for themselves but for the human family they would pass life to. We inherit a human nature wounded by that loss, inclined to sin and subject to death. This is original sin, and we contract it, we do not personally commit it.\n\nThis is why we are baptized. Baptism washes away original sin and restores the life of grace. The good news is larger than the bad: Saint Paul says that where sin abounded, grace abounded all the more. In Christ, the new Adam, what was lost is more than restored.",
