    formationText: "Some Old Testament texts speak of total war against the peoples of Canaan, often using the sweeping, formulaic language of ancient warfare. These passages are genuinely difficult, and the Church does not pretend otherwise. We hold firmly that God is just and that the deliberate killing of the innocent is always wrong. We also recognize that Scripture reveals God\u2019s will gradually and that human authors expressed it within the limits of their age.\n\nWe must let the whole of revelation interpret the parts. The Book of Wisdom already insists that God loves all he has made and judges with mercy and restraint. And the final word is Jesus, who refuses the sword, forgives his executioners, and lays down his own life. When a passage troubles us, we bring it to him, trusting that the God revealed on the cross is the true face of the God of Israel.",
    reflection: "When a part of Scripture unsettles you, can you bring it honestly to God rather than either ignoring it or losing heart?",
