    formationText: "It is true that we can and should turn to God for mercy at any moment, and he hears us. So why a priest? Because this is how Jesus chose to give his forgiveness. After the Resurrection he breathed on the apostles and said, whose sins you forgive are forgiven. He entrusted a real ministry of reconciliation to his Church.\n\nThere is great mercy in this. The priest does not forgive by his own power; Christ forgives through him. And we humans need to hear the words out loud, to name our failures honestly and receive a sure assurance of pardon. Confession is not a barrier between us and God. It is Jesus meeting us personally, through his Church, with words we can actually hear: your sins are forgiven.",
