    formationText: "When Jesus says, call no one on earth your father, he is warning against giving anyone the place that belongs to God, and against leaders who crave titles and honor. He is not abolishing the word, for Scripture itself keeps using it. Saint Paul calls himself a spiritual father to the Corinthians, saying he became their father in Christ through the Gospel.\n\nWe rightly call our biological fathers father, and the Church extends this naturally to priests, who exercise a spiritual fatherhood, begetting and nourishing God\u2019s life in us. All such fatherhood is a share in the one Fatherhood of God. The title is not a denial of that truth but a reminder of it.",
