    formationText: "Nothing unclean can enter heaven, yet many who die truly love God are still not fully free of the effects of sin. Purgatory is the name the Church gives to the final purification of these souls, who are certainly saved but who need to be made completely ready for the joy of seeing God face to face. It is entirely about heaven, not hell.\n\nThe roots are biblical. Scripture speaks of being saved as through fire, and of prayer for the dead so that they may be freed from sin, which makes no sense unless purification after death is possible. This is why Catholics pray for the dead with such hope. Purgatory is mercy, the loving way God finishes in us the work he began.",
