    category: "Catholic vs Common Misunderstandings",
    summary: "An indulgence has never been permission to sin or a way to buy forgiveness. It is the Church applying Christ\u2019s mercy to the effects of sin.",
    formationText: "Even after a sin is forgiven, its effects can linger in us, like a wound that still needs healing after a wrong is pardoned. An indulgence is the Church, using the authority Christ gave her, drawing on the infinite merits of Christ and the saints to help heal those lingering effects, in this life or for the souls in purgatory. It always presupposes that the sin is already forgiven.\n\nIndulgences are received through prayer, charity, and acts of devotion, never bought. The historical abuse of selling them was a real scandal, and the Church corrected it. Rightly understood, an indulgence is simply the family of the Church pouring out Christ\u2019s mercy on her members to make us whole.",
