    category: "Prayer",
    summary: "God always hears, and he always answers, though not always in the way or the timing we expect.",
    formationText: "Jesus promised that the one who asks receives, yet we all know the ache of prayers that seem to go nowhere. Scripture is honest about this. Sometimes we ask for something that would not truly be good for us. Sometimes God is giving us something better, or working on a longer timeline than we can see. And sometimes, as with Saint Paul's thorn, the answer is grace to endure rather than the removal of the burden.\n\nGod is a loving Father, not a vending machine. An unanswered prayer is not a closed door but an invitation to keep trusting, to keep asking, and to let our desires be slowly purified until we want what he wants. Often the deepest answer to prayer is not a changed circumstance but a changed heart.",
    reflection: "Is there a prayer you have stopped praying because it felt unanswered? What would it take to bring it back to God with trust?",
    scriptureReferences: ["Matthew 7:7-11", "2 Corinthians 12:8-9", "James 4:3"],
    catechismReferences: ["CCC 2735", "CCC 2737", "CCC 2739"],
