    formationText: "Some imagine the Mass is a human tradition added on later, but its shape comes straight from Scripture. At the Last Supper, Jesus took bread and wine, gave thanks, and commanded, do this in remembrance of me. The first Christians obeyed, gathering for the breaking of the bread and the prayers. Saint Paul hands on the words of consecration as something he received from the Lord himself.\n\nEven the structure of the Mass is scriptural: we listen to the Word, then share the Eucharist, just as the risen Jesus opened the Scriptures and then was known in the breaking of the bread on the road to Emmaus. The prophet Malachi even foretold a pure offering made among all nations. The Mass is the Bible come to life around the altar.",
