    formationText: "Holiness can sound distant, as if it were only for canonized saints. But God says to all his people, be holy, for I am holy. Holiness simply means belonging fully to God and letting his love transform us from the inside. It is less about flawless behavior and more about a heart turned toward him.\n\nThis is the universal call. The Church teaches that everyone, in every walk of life, is called to the fullness of Christian love, which is holiness. You do not need to enter a monastery or do extraordinary things. You need to love God and your neighbor where you are, day by day, allowing grace to make you more like Christ.",
