    formationText: "Every saint was once a beginner. Many had real flaws, dramatic failures, or unremarkable lives. What set them apart was not raw talent or natural goodness but a willingness to keep saying yes to God, to get up after falling, and to let grace do its slow work. Saint Paul reminds us that God chose us in Christ to be holy, and he finishes what he begins in us.\n\nThis is deeply hopeful. Sainthood is not a prize for the elite; it is the destiny God offers to every baptized person, including you. The path is made of small, faithful acts of love, repeated over a lifetime and carried by grace. Heaven is full of ordinary people who simply did not give up on God.",
