    formationText: "For forty days before Easter, the Church enters Lent, echoing the forty days Jesus spent fasting in the desert. Through prayer, fasting, and almsgiving, we make room in our lives for God, face our sins honestly, and rediscover our need for the Savior. It is not a season of gloom but of preparation, like clearing and tilling soil so that new life can grow.\n\nLent has a clear goal: Easter. The little sacrifices, the extra prayer, the acts of charity are not ends in themselves. They open our hearts so that when we celebrate the Resurrection, the joy is real and deep. Now is the acceptable time, Saint Paul says, the day of salvation.",
