    formationText: "You may have heard a Catholic say, offer it up. Behind that simple phrase is a beautiful truth. When we accept a hardship, a disappointment, or a small sacrifice and consciously give it to God in union with Jesus on the cross, it stops being wasted suffering. It becomes a prayer, an act of love, even a help to others. Saint Paul says he rejoices in his sufferings for the sake of Christ's body.\n\nThis does not mean we go looking for misery, nor that we earn God's love by suffering. It means nothing in our lives is too small to offer. A patient hour, an aching back, a missed comfort, all of it can be lifted up and joined to the one perfect offering of Christ, becoming part of his redeeming love at work in the world.",
