    formationText: "Confirmation deepens and completes the grace of Baptism. Through the anointing with sacred chrism and the laying on of hands by the bishop, the Holy Spirit is poured out more fully, sealing us and strengthening us as witnesses to Christ. We see the pattern in the early Church, where the apostles laid hands on the newly baptized and they received the Holy Spirit in a new way.\n\nAt Pentecost the same Spirit turned frightened disciples into bold witnesses who went out to proclaim the Gospel. Confirmation gives us a share in that grace, equipping us not for a comfortable, hidden faith but for a living, courageous one. The gifts of the Holy Spirit, such as wisdom, understanding, counsel, fortitude, knowledge, piety, and fear of the Lord, take deeper root in us. Confirmation is not a graduation from the faith but a strengthening for the mission of living it fully.",
