    formationText: "We can and should pray to God directly at any moment, and he always hears us. So why priests? Because Jesus chose to act in his Church through chosen men. He called the apostles, gave them authority to teach, to forgive sins, and to offer the Eucharist, saying do this in remembrance of me. Priests today share in that ministry through Holy Orders, standing in the person of Christ for his people. The priest does not replace Christ; Christ works through him.\n\nThe sacraments that need a priest, the Eucharist and Reconciliation above all, are precisely the ways Jesus chose to keep coming close to us. Through the priest, Christ feeds us with his Body, forgives our sins, blesses marriages, and anoints the sick. A priest is a servant, often weak and human like all of us, yet entrusted with holy gifts for the good of the whole Church. Far from being a barrier, the priesthood is one of the ways Christ the Good Shepherd continues to care for his flock in every generation.",
    reflection: "How does it change your view of the priesthood to see it as Christ shepherding his people through human hands?",
