    formationText: "Catholics honour Mary because of who God made her to be. The angel Gabriel greeted her as full of grace, and her cousin Elizabeth, filled with the Holy Spirit, cried out, blessed are you among women. Mary herself, inspired by the Spirit, prophesied that all generations would call her blessed. To honour Mary is simply to take these words of Scripture seriously and to love the woman God chose above all others.\n\nMary is the first and greatest disciple. She heard God's word, said yes with her whole life, stood by her Son at the cross, and prayed with the apostles at Pentecost. Honouring her is not a distraction from Christ but a path toward him, because everything about Mary leads to her Son. The God who gave us the commandment to honour our father and mother surely honours his own mother, and he invites us to do the same.",
    reflection: "When you read that all generations would call Mary blessed, how do you sense God inviting you to honour her too?",
